OL,3,CMan denies criminal damage after
OL,4,CWinston Churchill statue defaced with
OL,5,Cgraffiti
OL,7,FA man has denied criminal damage after
OL,8,Fgraffiti was sprayed on a statue of
OL,9,FSir Winston Churchill, branding the
OL,10,Fformer prime minister a "Zionist war
OL,11,Fcriminal".
OL,13,FThe bronze monument in Parliament
OL,14,FSquare, opposite the Houses of
OL,15,FParliament in Westminster, was defaced
OL,16,Fwith phrases including "Stop the
OL,17,FGenocide" and "Free Palestine".
OL,19,FFurther graffiti read "Never again is
OL,20,FNow" and "Globalise the Intifada"
OL,21,Fsprayed in red paint.
